column1: OMAP-24: Organ Mapping Antibody Panel (OMAP) for Multiplexed Antibody-Based Imaging of Human Pancreas with CyCIF

column2: Diane Saunders; Andrea J. Radtke; Ellen M. Quardokus

column24: Vasoactive intestinal peptide is expressed in nerve ganglia (both neuronal soma and axons), allowing visualization of pancreatic ganglia. It is also expressed in pancreatic islet cells.
Choline O-acetyltransferase stains cholinergic neurons (both synapses and soma; mostly parasympathetic), showing selective neuronal expression in the pancreas.
Nitric oxide sythase 1 (also known as neuronal nitric oxide synthase) stains a subeset of neurons. In the pancreas, it shows strong differential expression in neurons within pancreatic ganglia.
ELAVL3/4 is a pan-neuronal marker that stains all pancreatic neurons.
Neurofilament heavy chain stains nerve fibers throughout the pancreas.
Calcitonin related polypeptide alpha is expressed both soma and axons of neurons in the central and peripheral nervous system. In the pancreas, it is expressed in sensory nerve fibers primarily.
Tachykinin precursor 1 is expressed in sensory (afferent) nerves in the pancreas, as well as in a subset of neurons in intrapancreatic ganglia.
Synaptosome associated protein 25 is expressed in intrapancreatic ganglia, primarily in nerve fibers surrounding the neurons. It is also expressed heavily in islets in both alpha and beta cells.
Tyrosine hydroxylase is expressed in sympathetic (efferent) nerves in the pancreas.
Insulin is a hormone that is expressed in the beta cells of the pancreas, helping define the islet functional tissue unit.
Somatostatin is a hormone that is expressed in the delta cells of the pancreas, helping define the islet functional tissue unit.
UCHL1 is expressed throughout the pancreas in the ganglia, nerve fibers, and cytoplasm of islet cells.
Glucagon is a hormone that is expressed in the alpha cells of the pancreas, helping define the islet functional tissue unit.
Used for detection of rabbit VIP primary antibody (cycle 1).
Used for detection of goat NOS1 primary antibody (cycle 1).
